pageContext.claim: “No, I've been urgent [about coronavirus]. This is urgent for me, right from the beginning. You know that because I closed up our country to China.”
pageContext.analysis: Despite the alarm bells and increased intelligence briefings about the virus, Health and Human Services Secretary Alex Azar struggled to get Trump’s attention on the issue for weeks. Ultimately, Trump, along with other top government officials spent two months downplaying the coronavirus threat.
